  "prompt": "Sarees become main part of fashion industry\u2026what you say?",
  "response": "Sarees have indeed become a prominent part of the fashion industry, not just in countries like India and Bangladesh where they are traditional garments, but also internationally. They have gained recognition for their elegance, versatility, and cultural significance. Fashion designers and influencers have played a pivotal role in bringing sarees to a global audience by modernizing and incorporating them into contemporary fashion trends.\n\nThere are several factors contributing to the saree's popularity in the fashion world:\n\n1. **Cultural Heritage:** Sarees are rich in cultural history and symbolism, which appeals to many who appreciate the stories and traditions behind the garments.\n\n2. **Versatility:** Sarees can be styled in numerous ways, making them suitable for various occasions, from casual wear to formal events. Innovative draping techniques and blending with modern attire have expanded their appeal.\n\n3. **Celebrity Influence:** High-profile celebrities, both from South Asia and internationally, have embraced sarees, wearing them at major events and promoting them on social media.\n\n4. **Designer Innovation:** Fashion designers have been experimenting with materials, patterns, and draping methods to reinvent the saree, thereby making it more appealing to global consumers.\n\n5. **Sustainable Fashion:** Sarees often utilize handwoven textiles and traditional craftsmanship, aligning with the growing demand for sustainable and ethically produced fashion items.\n\n6. **Globalization:** The increasing interconnectedness of cultures has led to a greater appreciation and acceptance of traditional attire like sarees in different parts of the world.\n\nIn summary, sarees have firmly established themselves within the fashion industry, combining traditional appeal with modern innovation to become a beloved garment across the globe.",
